    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.40-41_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">40</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 26, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>We went back to the <del>e</del><add>E</add>xpo<del>d</del><add>s</add> ition day before yesterday. It was alot<sic>a lot</sic> o<del>c</del><add>f</add> fun.</p>
                
                <p>I am glad to here<sic>hear</sic> that Yo-Yo was glad to see you. How is she? I hope I can convince Mom and Dad to get me a dog.</p>
                
                <p>I hope you are having al<del>p</del><add>o</add>t<sic>a lot</sic> of <del>f</del> fun. I sure am. Wish you were here. We could have alot<sic>a lot</sic> of fun.</p>
                
                <p>Martha and I have been having alot<sic>a lot</sic> of fun.</p>
                
                <p>We have found a good set of twi<del/><add>n</add> beds for my room so when you come we won<del>,</del><add>'</add>t be kicking each other out of bed.</p>
                
                <p><del/>I bought quite a few book<del/><add>s</add>.</p>
                
                <p>I have been <del>dra<unclear/>w</del> drawing some pictu<del>e</del><add>r</add>es of boats and if you want me to I will send you some.</p>
                
                <p>Wish you <del>w<unclear/>e</del> were here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your <del>H<unclear>Ho</unclear>>orary <del>g</del><add>G</add></del>
                        Honorary Grandson</salute>
                
                    <signed>Stewart Aly</signed>
                    <signed>Stewart Aly</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
